    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="807"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d807">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">623.4131/41</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 4954</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-08">October 8,
                            1936</date>.<lb/>[Received October 13.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Embassy’s despatch No. 4720 of
                    September 14, 1936,<note n="41" xml:id="d807fn41">Not printed.</note>
                    anticipating the early signature to the Agreement between Great Britain and Peru
                    relating to Commerce and Navigation, I have the honor to enclose, in duplicate,
                    a copy of the official Spanish and <pb facs="1020" n="921" xml:id="pg_921"/>
                    English text of this document with protocols, signed at Lima on October 6,
                        1936.<note n="42" xml:id="d807fn42">For text, see Peru, Ministerio de
                        Relaciones Exteriores, <hi rend="italic">Memoria</hi>, April 13–October 22,
                        1936 (Lima, 1938), Apendice 20, p. 105; also British Cmd. 5288, Peru No. 1
                        (1936): <hi rend="italic">Agreement Relating to Commerce and
                        Navigation</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>These pamphlets were received by the Embassy only a few minutes before the
                    closing of today’s air mail and therefore it has not been possible to examine
                    them with care.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Louis G. Dreyfus, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
